                     </desc>
                     <respons resp="dgrigoriou smayer tfruehwirth" locus="value"/>
                     <certainty cert="high" locus="value"/>
                  </interp>
                  <interp source="ph_046" xml:id="ana_046"><!-- link -->
                     <desc>In <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_1">W. H. Auden</rs>'s <ref target="acdh:amp-transcript__0039.xml">letter</ref> to <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_2">Stella Musulin</rs> from 28 April 1965, he sends her a German-language prose translation of his poem <rs type="lit_work" ref="#lit_work_id_60">"Joseph Weinheber"</rs>, made in collaboration with <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_157">Elizabeth Mayer</rs>. In the same letter, he asks Musulin to "check the translation for errors". The estate of Stella Musulin includes <ref target="acdh:amp-transcript__0046.xml">manuscript notes</ref>, in Stella Musulin's and <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_93">Elsa von Musulin</rs>'s hands, that relate to this translation; as well as a <ref target="acdh:amp-transcript__0047.xml">typescript of a reworked version</ref> of the German translation that incorporates these notes.</desc>
                     <respons resp="dgrigoriou smayer tfruehwirth" locus="value"/>
                     <certainty cert="high" locus="value"/>
                  </interp>
